{
  "texts": [
    "If we apply these principles to GenAI we find that: (i) the sources on which the results are based are hard to uncover, (ii) the models are no longer equally accessible and (iii) the results are difficult to reproduce.",
    "In other words, it does not qualify as FAIR science.",
    "In Norway, the National Committee for Research Ethics in Science and Technology (NENT) state in their Guidelines for Research Ethics in Science and Technology that: \"Researchers are responsible for conducting high-quality research characterised by scientific integrity, truthfulness, and accountability (…)\" (National Committee for Research & Ethics in Science and Technology [19]).",
    "When using a GenAI like ChatGPT to generate content, it becomes difficult to ensure high-quality and truthfulness, as this is no longer generated by you, but by the model.",
    "Also accountability becomes a point of discussion."
  ]
}